The report, <a href="https://www.pwc.com/gx/en/financial-services/pdf/pwc-elwood-annual-crypto-hedge-fund-report-may-2020.pdf" data-v-f87c67ca="">published</a> by PwC and Elwood Asset Management Services on Monday, shows that the total AUM of crypto hedge funds globally increased to over $2 billion in 2019 as compared to $1 billion in the previous year. Notably, 2019 saw bitcoin’s price jump over 90% as compared to 2018.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The percentage of crypto hedge funds with an AUM of over $20 million increased in 2019 from 19% to 35%. The average AUM increased from $21.9 million to $44 million, while the median AUM increased from $4.3 million to $8.2 million.&nbsp;
